[2026-05-02 09:41:25.16085] [526998] [debug] 	- [[XS]]
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.16087] [526998] [debug] 	- List::MoreUtils
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.16088] [526998] [debug] 	- TextAnalysisAndFormatting
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.16787] [526998] [debug] Token: Array::Iterator. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.16791] [526998] [debug] 	- Other modules discussed in the POD: Class::Iter, Class::Iterator, Data::Iter, Data::Iterator::EasyObj and Tie::Array::Iterable
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.17300] [526998] [debug] Token: Array::Merge::Unique. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.17303] [526998] [debug] 	- See also List::MoreUtils
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.17986] [526998] [debug] Token: Data::LnArray. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.17989] [526998] [debug] 	- Arrays with lots of access methods
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18842] [526998] [debug] Token: List::Util. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18845] [526998] [debug] 	- use List::Util 'any' or, better, 'first' (but don't use first() for finding 0 or undef!)
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18847] [526998] [debug] 	- And then 1 of
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18849] [526998] [debug] 	- if(any { $_ eq $thing } @values) ...
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18851] [526998] [debug] 	- if(any { $_ == $thing } @values) ...
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18852] [526998] [debug] 	- It's not limited to just string or number comparison of course; you can
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18854] [526998] [debug] 	put any arbitrary code in there. if(any { $_->is_close_to(123.45) } @values) ...
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18855] [526998] [debug] 	- Or
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18857] [526998] [debug] 	- If you don't like the XSUB call overhead of List::Util::any, there's
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18859] [526998] [debug] 	another (non-core) CPAN module List::Keywords which implements many of
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18860] [526998] [debug] 	the same utilities as real keywords with real opcodes, so they run
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18862] [526998] [debug] 	faster.
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18863] [526998] [debug] 	- use List::Keywords 'any';
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18865] [526998] [debug] 	- if(any { $_ eq $thing } @values) ...
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18866] [526998] [debug] 	- Or
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.18867] [526998] [debug] 	- if (grep { $_ eq $myval } @arr)
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.19048] [526998] [debug] Token: List::UtilsBy. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.19051] [526998] [debug] 	- Amazing!
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.19584] [526998] [debug] Token: Syntax::Operator::Zip. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.19587] [526998] [debug] 	- Provides 2 functions: mesh and zip, both of which are in List::Util
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.19589] [526998] [debug] 	- Also, List::UtilsBy contains zip_by and unzip_by
[2026-05-02 09:41:25.19802] [526998] [info] --------------------------------------------------
