[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13113] [526998] [info] Topic: id: 41. html_id: 410000. title: CpanFile
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13122] [526998] [debug] 	o See also
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13124] [526998] [debug] 	- [[CPAN]]
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13125] [526998] [debug] 	- LicenceStuff
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13127] [526998] [debug] 	- SecurityPolicy
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13134] [526998] [debug] 	<pre>
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13136] [526998] [debug] 	The docs here were copied from Google's Gemini, when I asked it how to generate a cpanfile
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13137] [526998] [debug] 	**1. Manual Creation**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13139] [526998] [debug] 	* **Create a file named `cpanfile`:** This file will reside in the root directory of your project.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13140] [526998] [debug] 	* **Add dependencies:**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13142] [526998] [debug] 	* Each line in the `cpanfile` represents a dependency.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13143] [526998] [debug] 	* Use the following syntax: `require 'ModuleName';`
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13145] [526998] [debug] 	* Example
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13146] [526998] [debug] 	```perl
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13148] [526998] [debug] 	require 'JSON';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13149] [526998] [debug] 	require 'Template';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13151] [526998] [debug] 	require 'DateTime';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13152] [526998] [debug] 	require 'DBIx::Class';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13154] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13155] [526998] [debug] 	**2. Using `Mojolicious::Command::Author::generate::cpanfile`**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13157] [526998] [debug] 	* **Install the Mojolicious framework (if not already installed):**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13158] [526998] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13160] [526998] [debug] 	cpanm Mojolicious
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13161] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13162] [526998] [debug] 	* **Generate the `cpanfile`:**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13164] [526998] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13165] [526998] [debug] 	mojo generate cpanfile
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13167] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13168] [526998] [debug] 	This command analyzes your Perl source code files (usually located in the `lib` directory) to identify used modules and generates the `cpanfile` accordingly.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13170] [526998] [debug] 	**3. Using Carton**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13171] [526998] [debug] 	* **Install Carton:**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13172] [526998] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13174] [526998] [debug] 	cpanm Carton
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13175] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13177] [526998] [debug] 	* **Create a `cpanfile`:**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13178] [526998] [debug] 	```bash
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13179] [526998] [debug] 	carton init
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13181] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13182] [526998] [debug] 	This creates a basic `cpanfile` with some default settings. You can then manually add your project's specific dependencies.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13184] [526998] [debug] 	**Key Considerations**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13185] [526998] [debug] 	* **Version Constraints:** You can specify version constraints for your dependencies to ensure compatibility and stability. For example
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13187] [526998] [debug] 	```perl
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13188] [526998] [debug] 	require 'Module::Name' => '>= 1.2.3';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13189] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13191] [526998] [debug] 	* **Local Modules:** If you have local modules that are not on CPAN, you can add them to your `cpanfile` using special directives.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13192] [526998] [debug] 	* **Testing:** After generating your `cpanfile`, always test your application to ensure all dependencies are installed correctly and your application functions as expected.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13194] [526998] [debug] 	**Example `cpanfile`**
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13195] [526998] [debug] 	```perl
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13196] [526998] [debug] 	require 'JSON';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13198] [526998] [debug] 	require 'Template' => '>= 2.18';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13199] [526998] [debug] 	require 'DateTime';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13201] [526998] [debug] 	require 'DBIx::Class';
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13202] [526998] [debug] 	require 'MyLocalModule'; # A hypothetical local module
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13204] [526998] [debug] 	```
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13205] [526998] [debug] 	By using a `cpanfile`, you can easily manage and install the necessary dependencies for your Perl projects, making your development process more efficient and reproducible.
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13207] [526998] [debug] 	</pre>
[2026-05-02 09:41:26.13211] [526998] [info] --------------------------------------------------
