[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86015] [526998] [debug] 	- NetworkProgramming
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86017] [526998] [debug] 	- TextAnalysisAndFormatting - For Regexp::Grammars
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86019] [526998] [debug] 	- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Regular_expressions
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86025] [526998] [debug] 	- https://perldoc.perl.org/ - PerlDoc
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86027] [526998] [debug] 	<pre>
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86028] [526998] [debug] 	>    for (@numbers) {
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86030] [526998] [debug] 	>       say "$_ is a single-digit number" if m/^\d$/;
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86031] [526998] [debug] 	>    }
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86033] [526998] [debug] 	Variant
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86034] [526998] [debug] 	say "$_ is a single-digit number"
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86035] [526998] [debug] 	for grep m{\A \d \Z}aax, @numbers;
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86037] [526998] [debug] 	Also, never forget the aa-modifiers if you want to limit \d to [0-9].
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86038] [526998] [debug] 	perl -E 'say "\x{0660}\n" =~ /^\d$/'
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86040] [526998] [debug] 	1
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86041] [526998] [debug] 	And use \z if the newline is undesired.
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.86042] [526998] [debug] 	</pre>
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.87001] [526998] [debug] Token: Regexp::Common. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:30.87004] [526998] [debug] 	- Aka Regex::Common
