[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11824] [526998] [debug] Token: Syntax::Keyword::Dynamically. Extras:
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11826] [526998] [debug] 	- Effectively
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11827] [526998] [debug] 	{
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11829] [526998] [debug] 	my $old = $VAR;
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11830] [526998] [debug] 	$VAR = "new value";
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11832] [526998] [debug] 	...
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11833] [526998] [debug] 	$VAR = $old;
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11835] [526998] [debug] 	}
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.11836] [526998] [debug] 	- Except that the old value will also be restored in the case of exceptions, go to, next/last/redo or similar ways to leave the controlling block scope.
