[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13913] [526998] [debug] 	- If a third-party requests a CVE we will ensure that they have reached out to perl-security (or the CPAN author) first and facilitate a discussion if necessary
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13914] [526998] [debug] 	The CVE.org CNA record also provides the email address to request a CVE
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13916] [526998] [debug] 	number.
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13917] [526998] [debug] 	https://www.cve.org/PartnerInformation/ListofPartners/partner/CPANSec
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13919] [526998] [debug] 	Additional details are available in the CNA disclosure policy.
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13920] [526998] [debug] 	https://security.metacpan.org/docs/cna-disclosure-policy.html
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13921] [526998] [debug] 	Stig Palmquist (STIGTSP), Timothy Legge (TIMLEGGE) and Breno G. de Oliveira
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13923] [526998] [debug] 	(GARU) are administering the CNA.  If you are interested in helping or
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.13924] [526998] [debug] 	learning more please contact us at cna@security.metacpan.org.
[2026-05-02 09:41:31.15090] [526998] [info] --------------------------------------------------
